<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>The Acolyte of Affliction</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: The Acolyte of Affliction">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white>
<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Level:</font></b> 68-68<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Sociality:</b></font> Social<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Classification:</b></font> Rare_Monster<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Known Habitats:</b></font> Plane of Torment<br>









<br><b><font color=#d2d200>Description:</b></font><br>- Spawns a number of Construct Seedlings to assist him.<BR>- Magic Slowable<BR><BR><b>Spawn and Scouting</b><BR><BR>As with all non-stomach minis in Torment, The Acolyte of Affliction is difficult to scout. You can only track him from a bit of the way in to the zone. While you can invis past the crows, there are see invis mobs on the walkways. You need to pacify your way in close enough and then track from there. Most guilds will only kill Torment minis on the way to killing Saryrn because they often will drop no loot.<BR><BR>He is a 3 day spawn.<BR><BR><b>What You Need</b><BR><BR>The Acolyte of Affliction can be killed by 18 or more moderately geared players. Because he often drops no loot though, he is normally only killed on the way to fighting Saryrn. So typically he is killed by 40+.<BR><BR><b>Preparation</b><BR><BR>Standard buffs are okay for this fight. There are no resistances that you need to worry about. Pull him outside of his room and wall him as you would most other mobs.<BR><BR>The pull is the trickiest part of the fight. The other mobs in his room don't like to separate from him so two feign death pullers should be used. Just keep feigning and getting back up until you have sufficient distance between him and his adds and have the second puller bring him to the raid.<BR><BR><b>The Fight</b><BR><BR>During the fight Salczek will spawn a few Construct Seedlings to aid him. These are lower level adds and should not be much of a hassle. You can crowd control them, just be ready for them. Let the crowd control team deal with the adds and focus on dropping the Acolyte. It is also not uncommon for the pullers to have problems seperating him from other mobs in his room. Be prepared for him to come with an add or two in addition to his pets.<BR><BR>His melee output is decent (1500ish) but he is slowable (mitigated) by magic. A 3 cleric complete heal chain is plenty. If you are killing the Acolyte you are likely on your way to kill Saryrn. In this case you might want to use the same rotation that you plan on using for Saryrn for practice.<BR><BR>He has relatively low hit points, so even if things go poorly you should be able to zerg him down before he kills everyone.<BR><BR><b>Loot</b><BR><BR>Like all of the mini-bosses in the Plane of Torment, he can drop up to 2 loots, or none at all. He can also drop spectral parchments. His loots are decent when he does drop them, but nothing spectacular. For this reason he is normally only killed on the way up to Saryrn.<br>

<br><b>Known Drops</b>:<br>

